A\cos(\theta) + B\sin (\theta) = R\cos( \theta + \alpha)
A, B, R \text{ and } \alpha
\cos(\theta)
\sin(\theta)
\theta
 A\cos\theta+B\sin\theta = R\cos(\theta + \alpha)\\ A\cos\theta+B\sin\theta = R\left(\cos\theta\cos\alpha-\sin\theta\sin\alpha\right)\\ \left(R\cos\alpha-A\right)\cos\theta = \left(R\sin\alpha+B\right)\sin\theta\\ 
 \theta = 0\implies R\cos\alpha-A=0 \\ \theta = \frac{\pi}{2}\implies R\sin\alpha+B=0 
\theta=0
A=R\cos\alpha
A\cos\theta +B\sin \theta=R\cos(\theta+\alpha)=R\cos\theta\cos\alpha-R\sin\theta\sin \alpha
\theta=90^{\circ}=\frac {\pi}2\text{ radians}
B=-R\sin\alpha
